v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

53void Print(Tagged<Object> obj) {
54 // Output into debugger's command window if a debugger is attached.
55 DbgStdoutStream dbg_os;
56 Print(obj, dbg_os);
57 dbg_os << std::flush;
58
59 StdoutStream os;
60 Print(obj, os);
61 os << std::flush;
62}
63
64void Print(Tagged<Object> obj, std::ostream& os) {
65 if (IsSmi(obj)) {
66 os << "Smi: " << std::hex << "0x" << Smi::ToInt(obj);
67 os << std::dec << " (" << Smi::ToInt(obj) << ")\n";
68 } else {
69 Cast<HeapObject>(obj)->HeapObjectPrint(os);
70 }
71}

75#define AS_PTR(x) reinterpret_cast<void*>(x)
76#define AS_OBJ(x) Brief(Tagged<Object>(x))
77
78void PrintFunctionCallbackInfo(Address* implicit_args, Address* js_args,
79 Address length, std::ostream& os) {
80 using FCA = FunctionCallbackArguments;
81
82 static_assert(FCA::kArgsLength == 6);
83 os << "FunctionCallbackInfo: " //
84 << "\n - isolate: " << AS_PTR(implicit_args[FCA::kIsolateIndex])
85 << "\n - return_value: " << AS_OBJ(implicit_args[FCA::kReturnValueIndex])
86 << "\n - target: " << AS_OBJ(implicit_args[FCA::kTargetIndex])
87 << "\n - new_target: " << AS_OBJ(implicit_args[FCA::kNewTargetIndex])
88 << "\n - holder: " << AS_OBJ(implicit_args[FCA::kHolderIndex])
89
90 << "\n - argc: " << length //
91 << "\n - receiver: " << AS_OBJ(js_args[0]);
92
93 constexpr int kMaxArgs = 4;
94 for (int i = 0; i < std::min(static_cast<int>(length), kMaxArgs); i++) {
95 os << "\n - arg[" << i << "]: " << AS_OBJ(js_args[i]);
96 }
97 os << "\n";
98}
99
100void PrintPropertyCallbackInfo(Address* args, std::ostream& os) {
101 using PCA = internal::PropertyCallbackArguments;
102
103 static_assert(PCA::kArgsLength == 8);
104 os << "PropertyCallbackInfo: " //
105 << "\n - isolate: " << AS_PTR(args[PCA::kIsolateIndex])
106 << "\n - return_value: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kReturnValueIndex])
107 << "\n - should_throw: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex])
108 << "\n - holder: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kHolderIndex])
109 << "\n - holderV2: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kHolderV2Index])
110 << "\n - data: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kDataIndex]) //
111 << "\n - property_key: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kPropertyKeyIndex])
112 << "\n - receiver: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kThisIndex]);
113
114 // In case it's a setter call there will be additional |value| parameter,
115 // print it as a raw pointer to avoid crashing.
116 os << "\n - value?: " << AS_PTR(args[PCA::kArgsLength]);
117 os << "\n";
118}
119
120#undef AS_PTR
121#undef AS_OBJ

125void PrintFunctionCallbackInfo(void* function_callback_info) {
126 using FCI = v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>;
127 FCI& info = *reinterpret_cast<FCI*>(function_callback_info);
128
129 // |values| points to the first argument after the receiver.
130 Address* js_args = info.values_ - 1;
131
132 // Output into debugger's command window if a debugger is attached.
133 DbgStdoutStream dbg_os;
134 PrintFunctionCallbackInfo(info.implicit_args_, js_args, info.length_, dbg_os);
135 dbg_os << std::flush;
136
137 StdoutStream os;
138 PrintFunctionCallbackInfo(info.implicit_args_, js_args, info.length_, os);
139 os << std::flush;
140}
141
142void PrintPropertyCallbackInfo(void* property_callback_info) {
143 using PCI = v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<v8::Value>;
144 PCI& info = *reinterpret_cast<PCI*>(property_callback_info);
145
146 // Output into debugger's command window if a debugger is attached.
147 DbgStdoutStream dbg_os;
148 PrintPropertyCallbackInfo(info.args_, dbg_os);
149 dbg_os << std::flush;
150
151 StdoutStream os;
152 PrintPropertyCallbackInfo(info.args_, os);
153 os << std::flush;
154}

158void PrintHeapObjectHeaderWithoutMap(Tagged<HeapObject> object,
159 std::ostream& os, const char* id) {
160 PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase();
161 os << reinterpret_cast<void*>(object.ptr()) << ": [";
162 if (id != nullptr) {
163 os << id;
164 } else {
165 os << object->map(cage_base)->instance_type();
166 }
167 os << "]";
168 if (ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(object)) {
169 os << " in ReadOnlySpace";
170 }
171}

173template <typename T>
174void PrintDictionaryContents(std::ostream& os, Tagged<T> dict) {
175 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
176 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
177
178 if (dict->Capacity() == 0) {
179 return;
180 }
181
182#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY
183 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolateFromWritableObject(dict);
184 // IterateEntries for SwissNameDictionary needs to create a handle.
185 HandleScope scope(isolate);
186#endif
187 for (InternalIndex i : dict->IterateEntries()) {
188 Tagged<Object> k;
189 if (!dict->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
190 os << "\n ";
191 if (IsString(k)) {
192 Cast<String>(k)->PrintUC16(os);
193 } else {
194 os << Brief(k);
195 }
196 os << ": " << Brief(dict->ValueAt(i)) << " ";
197 dict->DetailsAt(i).PrintAsSlowTo(os, !T::kIsOrderedDictionaryType);
198 }
199}

203 Tagged<HeapObject>(this)->PrintHeader(os, id);

206void HeapObject::PrintHeader(std::ostream& os, const char* id) {
207 PrintHeapObjectHeaderWithoutMap(*this, os, id);
208 PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase();
209 if (!SafeEquals(GetReadOnlyRoots().meta_map())) {
210 os << "\n - map: " << Brief(map(cage_base));
211 }

214void HeapObject::HeapObjectPrint(std::ostream& os) {
215 PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase();
216
217 InstanceType instance_type = map(cage_base)->instance_type();
218
219 if (instance_type < FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE) {
220 Cast<String>(*this)->StringPrint(os);
221 os << "\n";
222 return;
223 }
224
225 // Skip invalid trusted objects. Technically it'd be fine to still handle
226 // them below since we only print the objects, but such an object will
227 // quickly lead to out-of-sandbox segfaults and so fuzzers will complain.
228 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsTrustedObject(instance_type) &&
229 !OutsideSandboxOrInReadonlySpace(*this)) {
230 os << "<Invalid TrustedObject (outside trusted space)>\n";
231 return;
232 }
233
234 switch (instance_type) {
235 case AWAIT_CONTEXT_TYPE:
236 case BLOCK_CONTEXT_TYPE:
237 case CATCH_CONTEXT_TYPE:
238 case DEBUG_EVALUATE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
239 case EVAL_CONTEXT_TYPE:
240 case FUNCTION_CONTEXT_TYPE:
241 case MODULE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
242 case SCRIPT_CONTEXT_TYPE:
243 case WITH_CONTEXT_TYPE:
244 Cast<Context>(*this)->ContextPrint(os);
245 break;
246 case NATIVE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
247 Cast<NativeContext>(*this)->NativeContextPrint(os);
248 break;
249 case HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
250 Cast<ObjectHashTable>(*this)->ObjectHashTablePrint(os);
251 break;
252 case NAME_TO_INDEX_HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
253 Cast<NameToIndexHashTable>(*this)->NameToIndexHashTablePrint(os);
254 break;
255 case REGISTERED_SYMBOL_TABLE_TYPE:
256 Cast<RegisteredSymbolTable>(*this)->RegisteredSymbolTablePrint(os);
257 break;
258 case ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
259 Cast<OrderedHashMap>(*this)->OrderedHashMapPrint(os);
260 break;
261 case ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
262 Cast<OrderedHashSet>(*this)->OrderedHashSetPrint(os);
263 break;
264 case ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
265 Cast<OrderedNameDictionary>(*this)->OrderedNameDictionaryPrint(os);
266 break;
267 case NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
268 Cast<NameDictionary>(*this)->NameDictionaryPrint(os);
269 break;
270 case GLOBAL_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
271 Cast<GlobalDictionary>(*this)->GlobalDictionaryPrint(os);
272 break;
273 case SIMPLE_NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
274 Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->FixedArrayPrint(os);
275 break;
276 case NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
277 Cast<NumberDictionary>(*this)->NumberDictionaryPrint(os);
278 break;
279 case EPHEMERON_HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
280 Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(*this)->EphemeronHashTablePrint(os);
281 break;
282 case TRANSITION_ARRAY_TYPE:
283 Cast<TransitionArray>(*this)->TransitionArrayPrint(os);
284 break;
285 case FILLER_TYPE:
286 os << "filler";
287 break;
288 case JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE:
289 case JS_ARRAY_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
290 case JS_CONTEXT_EXTENSION_OBJECT_TYPE:
291 case JS_ERROR_TYPE:
292 case JS_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
293 case JS_MAP_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
294 case JS_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
295 case JS_PROMISE_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
296 case JS_REG_EXP_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
297 case JS_SET_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
298 case JS_SET_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
299 case JS_SPECIAL_API_OBJECT_TYPE:
300 case JS_STRING_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
301 case JS_TYPED_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
302 Cast<JSObject>(*this)->JSObjectPrint(os);
303 break;
304#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
305 case WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_TYPE:
306 Cast<WasmTrustedInstanceData>(*this)->WasmTrustedInstanceDataPrint(os);
307 break;
308 case WASM_DISPATCH_TABLE_TYPE:
309 Cast<WasmDispatchTable>(*this)->WasmDispatchTablePrint(os);
310 break;
311 case WASM_VALUE_OBJECT_TYPE:
312 Cast<WasmValueObject>(*this)->WasmValueObjectPrint(os);
313 break;
314 case WASM_EXCEPTION_PACKAGE_TYPE:
315 Cast<WasmExceptionPackage>(*this)->WasmExceptionPackagePrint(os);
316 break;
317#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
318 case INSTRUCTION_STREAM_TYPE:
319 Cast<InstructionStream>(*this)->InstructionStreamPrint(os);
320 break;
321 case CODE_TYPE:
322 Cast<Code>(*this)->CodePrint(os);
323 break;
324 case CODE_WRAPPER_TYPE:
325 Cast<CodeWrapper>(*this)->CodeWrapperPrint(os);
326 break;
327 case JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
328 case JS_SET_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
329 Cast<JSSetIterator>(*this)->JSSetIteratorPrint(os);
330 break;
331 case JS_MAP_KEY_ITERATOR_TYPE:
332 case JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
333 case JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
334 Cast<JSMapIterator>(*this)->JSMapIteratorPrint(os);
335 break;
336#define MAKE_TORQUE_CASE(Name, TYPE) \
337 case TYPE: \
338 Cast<Name>(*this)->Name##Print(os); \
339 break;
340 // Every class that has its fields defined in a .tq file and corresponds
341 // to exactly one InstanceType value is included in the following list.
342 TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_SINGLE_FULLY_DEFINED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
343 TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_MULTIPLE_FULLY_DEFINED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
344#undef MAKE_TORQUE_CASE
345
346 case ALLOCATION_SITE_TYPE:
347 Cast<AllocationSite>(*this)->AllocationSitePrint(os);
348 break;
349 case LOAD_HANDLER_TYPE:
350 Cast<LoadHandler>(*this)->LoadHandlerPrint(os);
351 break;
352 case STORE_HANDLER_TYPE:
353 Cast<StoreHandler>(*this)->StoreHandlerPrint(os);
354 break;
355 case FEEDBACK_METADATA_TYPE:
356 Cast<FeedbackMetadata>(*this)->FeedbackMetadataPrint(os);
357 break;
358 case BIG_INT_BASE_TYPE:
359 Cast<BigIntBase>(*this)->BigIntBasePrint(os);
360 break;
361 case JS_CLASS_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
362 case JS_PROMISE_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
363 case JS_REG_EXP_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
364 case JS_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
365#define TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH(Type, type, TYPE, Ctype) \
366 case TYPE##_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
367 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH)
368#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH
369 Cast<JSFunction>(*this)->JSFunctionPrint(os);
370 break;
371 case INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
372 case EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
373 case INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
374 case EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
375 case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
376 case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
377 case SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
378 case CONS_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
379 case EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
380 case SLICED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
381 case THIN_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
382 case SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
383 case CONS_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
384 case EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
385 case SLICED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
386 case THIN_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
387 case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
388 case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
389 case SHARED_SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
390 case SHARED_SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
391 case SHARED_EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
392 case SHARED_EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
393 case SHARED_UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
394 case SHARED_UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
395 case JS_LAST_DUMMY_API_OBJECT_TYPE:
396 // TODO(all): Handle these types too.
397 os << "UNKNOWN TYPE " << map()->instance_type();
398 UNREACHABLE();
399 }
400}

402template <typename T>
403void PrintByteArrayElements(std::ostream& os, const T* array) {
404 int length = array->length();
405 int i = 0;
406 while (i < length) {
407 os << " 0x" << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(4) << std::hex << i << ":";
408 int line_end = std::min(i + 16, length);
409 for (; i < line_end; ++i) {
410 os << " " << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(2) << std::hex
411 << static_cast<int>(array->get(i));
412 }
413 os << "\n";
414 }
415}

447bool JSObject::PrintProperties(std::ostream& os) {
448 if (HasFastProperties()) {
449 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descs = map()->instance_descriptors(GetIsolate());
450 int nof_inobject_properties = map()->GetInObjectProperties();
451 for (InternalIndex i : map()->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
452 os << "\n ";
453 descs->GetKey(i)->NamePrint(os);
454 os << ": ";
455 PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
456 switch (details.location()) {
457 case PropertyLocation::kField: {
458 FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(map(), details);
459 os << Brief(RawFastPropertyAt(field_index));
460 break;
461 }
462 case PropertyLocation::kDescriptor:
463 os << Brief(descs->GetStrongValue(i));
464 break;
465 }
466 os << " ";
467 details.PrintAsFastTo(os, PropertyDetails::kForProperties);
468 if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
469 os << " @ ";
470 FieldType::PrintTo(descs->GetFieldType(i), os);
471 int field_index = details.field_index();
472 if (field_index < nof_inobject_properties) {
473 os << ", location: in-object";
474 } else {
475 field_index -= nof_inobject_properties;
476 os << ", location: properties[" << field_index << "]";
477 }
478 } else {
479 os << ", location: descriptor";
480 }
481 }
482 return map()->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() > 0;
483 } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(*this)) {
484 PrintDictionaryContents(
485 os, Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*this)->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad));
486 } else if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
487 PrintDictionaryContents(os, property_dictionary_swiss());
488 } else {
489 PrintDictionaryContents(os, property_dictionary());
490 }
491 return true;
492}

496template <class T>
497bool IsTheHoleAt(Tagged<T> array, int index) {
498 return false;
499}
500
501template <>
502bool IsTheHoleAt(Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> array, int index) {
503 return array->is_the_hole(index);
504}
505
506template <class T>
507double GetScalarElement(Tagged<T> array, int index) {
508 if (IsTheHoleAt(array, index)) {
509 return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
510 }
511 return array->get_scalar(index);
512}
513
514template <class T>
515void DoPrintElements(std::ostream& os, Tagged<Object> object, int length) {
516 const bool print_the_hole = std::is_same_v<T, FixedDoubleArray>;
517 Tagged<T> array = Cast<T>(object);
518 if (length == 0) return;
519 int previous_index = 0;
520 double previous_value = GetScalarElement(array, 0);
521 double value = 0.0;
522 int i;
523 for (i = 1; i <= length; i++) {
524 if (i < length) value = GetScalarElement(array, i);
525 bool values_are_nan = std::isnan(previous_value) && std::isnan(value);
526 if (i != length && (previous_value == value || values_are_nan) &&
527 IsTheHoleAt(array, i - 1) == IsTheHoleAt(array, i)) {
528 continue;
529 }
530 os << "\n";
531 std::stringstream ss;
532 ss << previous_index;
533 if (previous_index != i - 1) {
534 ss << '-' << (i - 1);
535 }
536 os << std::setw(12) << ss.str() << ": ";
537 if (print_the_hole && IsTheHoleAt(array, i - 1)) {
538 os << "<the_hole>";
539 } else {
540 os << previous_value;
541 }
542 previous_index = i;
543 previous_value = value;
544 }
545}
546
547struct Fp16Printer {
548 uint16_t val;
549 explicit Fp16Printer(float f) : val(fp16_ieee_from_fp32_value(f)) {}
550 operator float() const { return fp16_ieee_to_fp32_value(val); }
551};
552
553template <typename ElementType>
554void PrintTypedArrayElements(std::ostream& os, const ElementType* data_ptr,
555 size_t length, bool is_on_heap) {
556 if (length == 0) return;
557 size_t previous_index = 0;
558 if (i::v8_flags.mock_arraybuffer_allocator && !is_on_heap) {
559 // Don't try to print data that's not actually allocated.
560 os << "\n 0-" << length << ": <mocked array buffer bytes>";
561 return;
562 }
563
564 ElementType previous_value = data_ptr[0];
565 ElementType value{0};
566 for (size_t i = 1; i <= length; i++) {
567 if (i < length) value = data_ptr[i];
568 if (i != length && previous_value == value) {
569 continue;
570 }
571 os << "\n";
572 std::stringstream ss;
573 ss << previous_index;
574 if (previous_index != i - 1) {
575 ss << '-' << (i - 1);
576 }
577 os << std::setw(12) << ss.str() << ": " << +previous_value;
578 previous_index = i;
579 previous_value = value;
580 }
581}
582
583template <typename T>
584void PrintFixedArrayElements(std::ostream& os, Tagged<T> array, int capacity,
585 Tagged<Object> (*get)(Tagged<T>, int)) {
586 // Print in array notation for non-sparse arrays.
587 if (capacity == 0) return;
588 Tagged<Object> previous_value = get(array, 0);
589 Tagged<Object> value;
590 int previous_index = 0;
591 int i;
592 for (i = 1; i <= capacity; i++) {
593 if (i < capacity) value = get(array, i);
594 if (previous_value == value && i != capacity) {
595 continue;
596 }
597 os << "\n";
598 std::stringstream ss;
599 ss << previous_index;
600 if (previous_index != i - 1) {
601 ss << '-' << (i - 1);
602 }
603 os << std::setw(12) << ss.str() << ": " << Brief(previous_value);
604 previous_index = i;
605 previous_value = value;
606 }
607}
608
609template <typename T>
610void PrintFixedArrayElements(std::ostream& os, Tagged<T> array) {
611 PrintFixedArrayElements<T>(
612 os, array, array->length(),
613 [](Tagged<T> xs, int i) { return Cast<Object>(xs->get(i)); });
614}
615
616void PrintDictionaryElements(std::ostream& os,
617 Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements) {
618 // Print some internal fields
619 Tagged<NumberDictionary> dict = Cast<NumberDictionary>(elements);
620 if (dict->requires_slow_elements()) {
621 os << "\n - requires_slow_elements";
622 } else {
623 os << "\n - max_number_key: " << dict->max_number_key();
624 }
625 PrintDictionaryContents(os, dict);
626}

628void PrintSloppyArgumentElements(std::ostream& os, ElementsKind kind,
629 Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements) {
630 Tagged<FixedArray> arguments_store = elements->arguments();
631 os << "\n 0: context: " << Brief(elements->context())
632 << "\n 1: arguments_store: " << Brief(arguments_store)
633 << "\n parameter to context slot map:";
634 for (int i = 0; i < elements->length(); i++) {
635 Tagged<Object> mapped_entry = elements->mapped_entries(i, kRelaxedLoad);
636 os << "\n " << i << ": param(" << i << "): " << Brief(mapped_entry);
637 if (IsTheHole(mapped_entry)) {
638 os << " in the arguments_store[" << i << "]";
639 } else {
640 os << " in the context";
641 }
642 }
643 if (arguments_store->length() == 0) return;
644 os << "\n }"
645 << "\n - arguments_store: " << Brief(arguments_store) << " "
646 << ElementsKindToString(arguments_store->map()->elements_kind()) << " {";
647 if (kind == FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS) {
648 PrintFixedArrayElements(os, arguments_store);
649 } else {
650 DCHECK_EQ(kind, SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS);
651 PrintDictionaryElements(os, arguments_store);
652 }
653}
654
655void PrintEmbedderData(IsolateForSandbox isolate, std::ostream& os,
656 EmbedderDataSlot slot) {
657 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
658 Tagged<Object> value = slot.load_tagged();
659 os << Brief(value);
660 void* raw_pointer;
661 if (slot.ToAlignedPointer(isolate, &raw_pointer)) {
662 os << ", aligned pointer: " << raw_pointer;
663 }
664}

668void JSObject::PrintElements(std::ostream& os) {
669 // Don't call GetElementsKind, its validation code can cause the printer to
670 // fail when debugging.
671 os << " - elements: " << Brief(elements()) << " {";
672 switch (map()->elements_kind()) {
673 case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
674 case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
675 case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
676 case HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
677 case HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
678 case HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
679 case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
680 case PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
681 case PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
682 case PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
683 case FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
684 case SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS: {
685 PrintFixedArrayElements(os, Cast<FixedArray>(elements()));
686 break;
687 }
688 case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
689 case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: {
690 DoPrintElements<FixedDoubleArray>(os, elements(), elements()->length());
691 break;
692 }
693
694#define PRINT_ELEMENTS(Type, type, TYPE, elementType) \
695 case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: { \
696 size_t length = Cast<JSTypedArray>(*this)->GetLength(); \
697 bool is_on_heap = Cast<JSTypedArray>(*this)->is_on_heap(); \
698 const elementType* data_ptr = \
699 static_cast<const elementType*>(Cast<JSTypedArray>(*this)->DataPtr()); \
700 PrintTypedArrayElements<elementType>(os, data_ptr, length, is_on_heap); \
701 break; \
702 }
703 TYPED_ARRAYS(PRINT_ELEMENTS)
704 RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(PRINT_ELEMENTS)
705#undef PRINT_ELEMENTS
706
707 case DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS:
708 case SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
709 PrintDictionaryElements(os, elements());
710 break;
711 case FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
712 case SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
713 PrintSloppyArgumentElements(os, map()->elements_kind(),
714 Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(elements()));
715 break;
716 case WASM_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
717 // WasmArrayPrint() should be called intead.
718 UNREACHABLE();
719 case NO_ELEMENTS:
720 break;
721 }
722 os << "\n }\n";
723}

727void JSObjectPrintHeader(std::ostream& os, Tagged<JSObject> obj,
728 const char* id) {
729 Isolate* isolate = obj->GetIsolate();
730 obj->PrintHeader(os, id);
731 // Don't call GetElementsKind, its validation code can cause the printer to
732 // fail when debugging.
733 os << " [";
734 if (obj->HasFastProperties()) {
735 os << "FastProperties";
736 } else {
737 os << "DictionaryProperties";
738 }
739 PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, obj);
740 os << "]\n - prototype: " << Brief(iter.GetCurrent());
741 os << "\n - elements: " << Brief(obj->elements()) << " ["
742 << ElementsKindToString(obj->map()->elements_kind());
743 if (obj->elements()->IsCowArray()) os << " (COW)";
744 os << "]";
745 Tagged<Object> hash = Object::GetHash(obj);
746 if (IsSmi(hash)) {
747 os << "\n - hash: " << Brief(hash);
748 }
749 if (obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount() > 0) {
750 os << "\n - embedder fields: " << obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount();
751 }
752}
753
754void JSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlotsPrintHeader(std::ostream& os,
755 Tagged<JSObject> obj,
756 const char* id = nullptr) {
757 JSObjectPrintHeader(os, obj, id);
758 os << "\n - cpp_heap_wrappable: "
759 << obj->ReadField<uint32_t>(
760 JSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlots::kCppHeapWrappableOffset);
761}
762
763void JSObjectPrintBody(std::ostream& os, Tagged<JSObject> obj,
764 bool print_elements = true) {
765 os << "\n - properties: ";
766 Tagged<Object> properties_or_hash = obj->raw_properties_or_hash(kRelaxedLoad);
767 if (!IsSmi(properties_or_hash)) {
768 os << Brief(properties_or_hash);
769 }
770 os << "\n - All own properties (excluding elements): {";
771 if (obj->PrintProperties(os)) os << "\n ";
772 os << "}\n";
773
774 if (print_elements) {
775 size_t length = IsJSTypedArray(obj) ? Cast<JSTypedArray>(obj)->GetLength()
776 : obj->elements()->length();
777 if (length > 0) obj->PrintElements(os);
778 }
779 int embedder_fields = obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount();
780 if (embedder_fields > 0) {
781 IsolateForSandbox isolate = GetIsolateForSandbox(obj);
782 os << " - embedder fields = {";
783 for (int i = 0; i < embedder_fields; i++) {
784 os << "\n ";
785 PrintEmbedderData(isolate, os, EmbedderDataSlot(obj, i));
786 }
787 os << "\n }\n";
788 }
789}

804void JSGeneratorObject::JSGeneratorObjectPrint(std::ostream& os) {
805 JSObjectPrintHeader(os, *this, "JSGeneratorObject");
806 os << "\n - function: " << Brief(function());
807 os << "\n - context: " << Brief(context());
808 os << "\n - receiver: " << Brief(receiver());
809 if (is_executing() || is_closed()) {
810 os << "\n - input: " << Brief(input_or_debug_pos());
811 } else {
812 DCHECK(is_suspended());
813 os << "\n - debug pos: " << Brief(input_or_debug_pos());
814 }
815 const char* mode = "(invalid)";
816 switch (resume_mode()) {
817 case kNext:
818 mode = ".next()";
819 break;
820 case kReturn:
821 mode = ".return()";
822 break;
823 case kThrow:
824 mode = ".throw()";
825 break;
826 }
827 os << "\n - resume mode: " << mode;
828 os << "\n - continuation: " << continuation();
829 if (is_closed()) os << " (closed)";
830 if (is_executing()) os << " (executing)";
831 if (is_suspended()) os << " (suspended)";
832 if (is_suspended()) {
833 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
834 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> fun_info = function()->shared();
835 if (fun_info->HasSourceCode()) {
836 Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(fun_info->script());
837 Tagged<String> script_name = IsString(script->name())
838 ? Cast<String>(script->name())
839 : GetReadOnlyRoots().empty_string();
840
841 os << "\n - source position: ";
842 // Can't collect source positions here if not available as that would
843 // allocate memory.
844 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolate();
845 if (fun_info->HasBytecodeArray() &&
846 fun_info->GetBytecodeArray(isolate)->HasSourcePositionTable()) {
847 os << source_position();
848 os << " (";
849 script_name->PrintUC16(os);
850 Script::PositionInfo info;
851 script->GetPositionInfo(source_position(), &info);
852 os << ", line " << info.line + 1;
853 os << ", column " << info.column + 1;
854 } else {
855 os << kUnavailableString;
856 }
857 os << ")";
858 }
859 }
860 os << "\n - register file: " << Brief(parameters_and_registers());
861 JSObjectPrintBody(os, *this);
862}

1001
1002template <typename T>
1003void PrintWeakArrayElements(std::ostream& os, T* array) {
1004 // Print in array notation for non-sparse arrays.
1005 Tagged<MaybeObject> previous_value =
1006 array->length() > 0 ? array->get(0) : Tagged<MaybeObject>(kNullAddress);
1007 Tagged<MaybeObject> value;
1008 int previous_index = 0;
1009 int i;
1010 for (i = 1; i <= array->length(); i++) {
1011 if (i < array->length()) value = array->get(i);
1012 if (previous_value == value && i != array->length()) {
1013 continue;
1014 }
1015 os << "\n";
1016 std::stringstream ss;
1017 ss << previous_index;
1018 if (previous_index != i - 1) {
1019 ss << '-' << (i - 1);
1020 }
1021 os << std::setw(12) << ss.str() << ": " << Brief(previous_value);
1022 previous_index = i;
1023 previous_value = value;
1024 }
1025}

1244namespace {
1245using DataPrinter = std::function<void(InternalIndex)>;
1246
1247// Prints the data associated with each key (but no headers or other meta
1248// data) in a hash table. Works on different hash table types, like the
1249// subtypes of HashTable and OrderedHashTable. |print_data_at| is given an
1250// index into the table (where a valid key resides) and prints the data at
1251// that index, like just the value (in case of a hash map), or value and
1252// property details (in case of a property dictionary). No leading space
1253// required or trailing newline required. It can be null/non-callable
1254// std::function to indicate that there is no associcated data to be printed
1255// (for example in case of a hash set).
1256template <typename T>
1257void PrintTableContentsGeneric(std::ostream& os, T* dict,
1258 DataPrinter print_data_at) {
1259 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1260 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
1261
1262 for (InternalIndex i : dict->IterateEntries()) {
1263 Tagged<Object> k;
1264 if (!dict->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
1265 os << "\n " << std::setw(12) << i.as_int() << ": ";
1266 if (IsString(k)) {
1267 Cast<String>(k)->PrintUC16(os);
1268 } else {
1269 os << Brief(k);
1270 }
1271 if (print_data_at) {
1272 os << " -> ";
1273 print_data_at(i);
1274 }
1275 }
1276}
1277
1278void PrintNameDictionaryFlags(std::ostream& os, Tagged<NameDictionary> dict) {
1279 if (dict->may_have_interesting_properties()) {
1280 os << "\n - may_have_interesting_properties";
1281 }
1282}
1283
1284// Used for ordered and unordered dictionaries.
1285template <typename T>
1286void PrintDictionaryContentsFull(std::ostream& os, T* dict) {
1287 os << "\n - elements: {";
1288 auto print_value_and_property_details = [&](InternalIndex i) {
1289 os << Brief(dict->ValueAt(i)) << " ";
1290 dict->DetailsAt(i).PrintAsSlowTo(os, !T::kIsOrderedDictionaryType);
1291 };
1292 PrintTableContentsGeneric(os, dict, print_value_and_property_details);
1293 os << "\n }\n";
1294}
1295
1296// Used for ordered and unordered hash maps.
1297template <typename T>
1298void PrintHashMapContentsFull(std::ostream& os, T* dict) {
1299 os << "\n - elements: {";
1300 auto print_value = [&](InternalIndex i) { os << Brief(dict->ValueAt(i)); };
1301 PrintTableContentsGeneric(os, dict, print_value);
1302 os << "\n }\n";
1303}
1304
1305// Used for ordered and unordered hash sets.
1306template <typename T>
1307void PrintHashSetContentsFull(std::ostream& os, T* dict) {
1308 os << "\n - elements: {";
1309 // Passing non-callable std::function as there are no values to print.
1310 PrintTableContentsGeneric(os, dict, nullptr);
1311 os << "\n }\n";
1312}

1314// Used for subtypes of OrderedHashTable.
1315template <typename T>
1316void PrintOrderedHashTableHeaderAndBuckets(std::ostream& os, T* table,
1317 const char* type) {
1318 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1319
1320 PrintHeapObjectHeaderWithoutMap(table, os, type);
1321 os << "\n - FixedArray length: " << table->length();
1322 os << "\n - elements: " << table->NumberOfElements();
1323 os << "\n - deleted: " << table->NumberOfDeletedElements();
1324 os << "\n - buckets: " << table->NumberOfBuckets();
1325 os << "\n - capacity: " << table->Capacity();
1326
1327 os << "\n - buckets: {";
1328 for (int bucket = 0; bucket < table->NumberOfBuckets(); bucket++) {
1329 Tagged<Object> entry = table->get(T::HashTableStartIndex() + bucket);
1330 DCHECK(IsSmi(entry));
1331 os << "\n " << std::setw(12) << bucket << ": " << Brief(entry);
1332 }
1333 os << "\n }";
1334}

1344}

1414void print_hex_byte(std::ostream& os, int value) {
1415 os << "0x" << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(2) << std::right << std::hex
1416 << (value & 0xff) << std::setfill(' ');
1417}
1418
1419void SwissNameDictionary::SwissNameDictionaryPrint(std::ostream& os) {
1420 this->PrintHeader(os, "SwissNameDictionary");
1421 os << "\n - meta table ByteArray: "
1422 << reinterpret_cast<void*>(this->meta_table().ptr());
1423 os << "\n - capacity: " << this->Capacity();
1424 os << "\n - elements: " << this->NumberOfElements();
1425 os << "\n - deleted: " << this->NumberOfDeletedElements();
1426
1427 std::ios_base::fmtflags sav_flags = os.flags();
1428 os << "\n - ctrl table (omitting buckets where key is hole value): {";
1429 for (int i = 0; i < this->Capacity() + kGroupWidth; i++) {
1430 ctrl_t ctrl = CtrlTable()[i];
1431
1432 if (ctrl == Ctrl::kEmpty) continue;
1433
1434 os << "\n " << std::setw(12) << std::dec << i << ": ";
1435 switch (ctrl) {
1436 case Ctrl::kEmpty:
1437 UNREACHABLE();
1438 case Ctrl::kDeleted:
1439 print_hex_byte(os, ctrl);
1440 os << " (= kDeleted)";
1441 break;
1442 case Ctrl::kSentinel:
1443 print_hex_byte(os, ctrl);
1444 os << " (= kSentinel)";
1445 break;
1446 default:
1447 print_hex_byte(os, ctrl);
1448 os << " (= H2 of a key)";
1449 break;
1450 }
1451 }
1452 os << "\n }";
1453
1454 os << "\n - enumeration table: {";
1455 for (int enum_index = 0; enum_index < this->UsedCapacity(); enum_index++) {
1456 int entry = EntryForEnumerationIndex(enum_index);
1457 os << "\n " << std::setw(12) << std::dec << enum_index << ": " << entry;
1458 }
1459 os << "\n }";
1460
1461 os << "\n - data table (omitting slots where key is the hole): {";
1462 for (int bucket = 0; bucket < this->Capacity(); ++bucket) {
1463 Tagged<Object> k;
1464 if (!this->ToKey(GetReadOnlyRoots(), bucket, &k)) continue;
1465
1466 Tagged<Object> value = this->ValueAtRaw(bucket);
1467 PropertyDetails details = this->DetailsAt(bucket);
1468 os << "\n " << std::setw(12) << std::dec << bucket << ": ";
1469 if (IsString(k)) {
1470 Cast<String>(k)->PrintUC16(os);
1471 } else {
1472 os << Brief(k);
1473 }
1474 os << " -> " << Brief(value);
1475 details.PrintAsSlowTo(os, false);
1476 }
1477 os << "\n }\n";
1478 os.flags(sav_flags);
1479}

1531void FeedbackCell::FeedbackCellPrint(std::ostream& os) {
1532 PrintHeader(os, "FeedbackCell");
1533 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
1534 if (map() == roots.no_closures_cell_map()) {
1535 os << "\n - no closures";
1536 } else if (map() == roots.one_closure_cell_map()) {
1537 os << "\n - one closure";
1538 } else if (map() == roots.many_closures_cell_map()) {
1539 os << "\n - many closures";
1540 } else {
1541 os << "\n - Invalid FeedbackCell map";
1542 }
1543 os << "\n - value: " << Brief(value());
1544 os << "\n - interrupt_budget: " << interrupt_budget();
1545#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1546 os << "\n - dispatch_handle: 0x" << std::hex << dispatch_handle() << std::dec;
1547 JSDispatchTable* jdt = IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table();
1548 if (dispatch_handle() != kNullJSDispatchHandle &&
1549 jdt->IsTieringRequested(dispatch_handle())) {
1550 os << "\n - tiering request ";
1551 if (Tagged<FeedbackVector> fbv;
1552 TryCast(value(), &fbv) && fbv->tiering_in_progress()) {
1553 os << "in_progress ";
1554 }
1555 jdt->PrintCurrentTieringRequest(dispatch_handle(),
1556 GetIsolateFromWritableObject(*this), os);
1557 }
1558
1559#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1560 os << "\n";
1561}

1571void FeedbackVectorSpec::FeedbackVectorSpecPrint(std::ostream& os) {
1572 os << " - slot_count: " << slot_count();
1573 if (slot_count() == 0) {
1574 os << " (empty)\n";
1575 return;
1576 }
1577
1578 for (int slot = 0; slot < slot_count();) {
1579 FeedbackSlotKind kind = GetKind(FeedbackSlot(slot));
1580 int entry_size = FeedbackMetadata::GetSlotSize(kind);
1581 DCHECK_LT(0, entry_size);
1582 os << "\n Slot #" << slot << " " << kind;
1583 slot += entry_size;
1584 }
1585 os << "\n";
1586}

1592

1594 while (iter.HasNext()) {

1610void FeedbackVector::FeedbackVectorPrint(std::ostream& os) {
1611 PrintHeader(os, "FeedbackVector");
1612 os << "\n - length: " << length();
1613 if (length() == 0) {
1614 os << " (empty)\n";
1615 return;
1616 }
1617
1618 os << "\n - shared function info: " << Brief(shared_function_info());
1619#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1620 os << "\n - tiering_in_progress: " << tiering_in_progress();
1621#else
1622 os << "\n - tiering state: " << tiering_state();
1623 if (has_optimized_code()) {
1624 os << "\n - optimized code: "
1625 << Brief(optimized_code(GetIsolateForSandbox(*this)));
1626 } else {
1627 os << "\n - no optimized code";
1628 }
1629 os << "\n - maybe has maglev code: " << maybe_has_maglev_code();
1630 os << "\n - maybe has turbofan code: " << maybe_has_turbofan_code();
1631#endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1632 os << "\n - osr_tiering_in_progress: " << osr_tiering_in_progress();
1633 os << "\n - invocation count: " << invocation_count();
1634 os << "\n - closure feedback cell array: ";
1635 closure_feedback_cell_array()->ClosureFeedbackCellArrayPrint(os);
1636
1637 FeedbackMetadataIterator iter(metadata());
1638 while (iter.HasNext()) {
1639 FeedbackSlot slot = iter.Next();
1640 FeedbackSlotKind kind = iter.kind();
1641
1642 os << "\n - slot " << slot << " " << kind << " ";
1643 FeedbackSlotPrint(os, slot);
1644
1645 int entry_size = iter.entry_size();
1646 if (entry_size > 0) os << " {";
1647 for (int i = 0; i < entry_size; i++) {
1648 FeedbackSlot slot_with_offset = slot.WithOffset(i);
1649 os << "\n [" << slot_with_offset.ToInt()
1650 << "]: " << Brief(Get(slot_with_offset));
1651 }
1652 if (entry_size > 0) os << "\n }";
1653 }
1654 os << "\n";
1655}

1657void FeedbackVector::FeedbackSlotPrint(std::ostream& os, FeedbackSlot slot) {
1658 FeedbackNexus nexus(GetIsolate(), *this, slot);
1659 nexus.Print(os);
1660}
1661
1662void FeedbackNexus::Print(std::ostream& os) {
1663 auto slot_kind = kind();
1664 switch (slot_kind) {
1665 case FeedbackSlotKind::kCall:
1666 case FeedbackSlotKind::kCloneObject:
1667 case FeedbackSlotKind::kHasKeyed:
1668 case FeedbackSlotKind::kInstanceOf:
1669 case FeedbackSlotKind::kTypeOf:
1670 case FeedbackSlotKind::kDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral:
1671 case FeedbackSlotKind::kStoreInArrayLiteral: {
1672 os << InlineCacheState2String(ic_state());
1673 break;
1674 }
1675 case FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadGlobalInsideTypeof:
1676 case FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadGlobalNotInsideTypeof:
1677 case FeedbackSlotKind::kStoreGlobalSloppy:
1678 case FeedbackSlotKind::kStoreGlobalStrict: {
1679 os << InlineCacheState2String(ic_state());
1680 if (ic_state() == InlineCacheState::MONOMORPHIC) {
1681 os << "\n ";
1682 if (GetFeedback().IsCleared()) {
1683 // Handler mode: feedback is the cleared value, extra is the handler.
1684 if (IsLoadGlobalICKind(slot_kind)) {
1685 LoadHandler::PrintHandler(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObjectOrSmi(),
1686 os);
1687 } else {
1688 StoreHandler::PrintHandler(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObjectOrSmi(),
1689 os);
1690 }
1691 } else if (IsPropertyCell(GetFeedback().GetHeapObjectOrSmi())) {
1692 os << Brief(GetFeedback());
1693 } else {
1694 // Lexical variable mode: the variable location is encoded in the SMI.
1695 int handler = GetFeedback().GetHeapObjectOrSmi().ToSmi().value();
1696 os << (IsLoadGlobalICKind(slot_kind) ? "Load" : "Store");
1697 os << "Handler(Lexical variable mode)(context ix = "
1698 << FeedbackNexus::ContextIndexBits::decode(handler)
1699 << ", slot ix = " << FeedbackNexus::SlotIndexBits::decode(handler)
1700 << ")";
1701 }
1702 }
1703 break;
1704 }
1705 case FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadKeyed:
1706 case FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadProperty: {
1707 os << InlineCacheState2String(ic_state());
1708 if (ic_state() == InlineCacheState::MONOMORPHIC) {
1709 os << "\n " << Brief(GetFeedback()) << ": ";
1710 if (GetFeedbackExtra().IsCleared()) {
1711 os << " <cleared>\n";
1712 break;
1713 }
1714 Tagged<Object> handler = GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObjectOrSmi();
1715 if (IsWeakFixedArray(handler) &&
1716 !Cast<WeakFixedArray>(handler)->get(0).IsCleared()) {
1717 handler = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(handler)->get(0).GetHeapObjectOrSmi();
1718 }
1719 LoadHandler::PrintHandler(handler, os);
1720 } else if (ic_state() == InlineCacheState::POLYMORPHIC) {
1721 Tagged<HeapObject> feedback = GetFeedback().GetHeapObject();
1722 Tagged<WeakFixedArray> array;
1723 if (IsName(feedback)) {
1724 os << " with name " << Brief(feedback);
1725 array = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObject());
1726 } else {
1727 array = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(feedback);
1728 }
1729 for (int i = 0; i < array->length(); i += 2) {
1730 os << "\n " << Brief(array->get(i)) << ": ";
1731 LoadHandler::PrintHandler(array->get(i + 1).GetHeapObjectOrSmi(), os);
1732 }
1733 }
1734 break;
1735 }
1736 case FeedbackSlotKind::kDefineNamedOwn:
1737 case FeedbackSlotKind::kDefineKeyedOwn:
1738 case FeedbackSlotKind::kSetNamedSloppy:
1739 case FeedbackSlotKind::kSetNamedStrict:
1740 case FeedbackSlotKind::kSetKeyedSloppy:
1741 case FeedbackSlotKind::kSetKeyedStrict: {
1742 os << InlineCacheState2String(ic_state());
1743 if (GetFeedback().IsCleared()) {
1744 os << "\n [cleared]";
1745 break;
1746 }
1747 if (ic_state() == InlineCacheState::MONOMORPHIC) {
1748 Tagged<HeapObject> feedback = GetFeedback().GetHeapObject();
1749 if (GetFeedbackExtra().IsCleared()) {
1750 os << " [cleared]\n";
1751 break;
1752 }
1753 if (IsName(feedback)) {
1754 os << " with name " << Brief(feedback);
1755 Tagged<WeakFixedArray> array =
1756 Cast<WeakFixedArray>(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObject());
1757 os << "\n " << Brief(array->get(0)) << ": ";
1758 if (array->get(1).IsCleared()) {
1759 os << "[cleared]\n";
1760 } else {
1761 Tagged<Object> handler = array->get(1).GetHeapObjectOrSmi();
1762 StoreHandler::PrintHandler(handler, os);
1763 }
1764 } else {
1765 os << "\n " << Brief(feedback) << ": ";
1766 StoreHandler::PrintHandler(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObjectOrSmi(),
1767 os);
1768 }
1769 } else if (ic_state() == InlineCacheState::POLYMORPHIC) {
1770 Tagged<HeapObject> feedback = GetFeedback().GetHeapObject();
1771 Tagged<WeakFixedArray> array;
1772 if (IsName(feedback)) {
1773 os << " with name " << Brief(feedback);
1774 array = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObject());
1775 } else {
1776 array = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(feedback);
1777 }
1778 for (int i = 0; i < array->length(); i += 2) {
1779 os << "\n " << Brief(array->get(i)) << ": ";
1780 if (!array->get(i + 1).IsCleared()) {
1781 StoreHandler::PrintHandler(array->get(i + 1).GetHeapObjectOrSmi(),
1782 os);
1783 }
1784 }
1785 }
1786 break;
1787 }
1788 case FeedbackSlotKind::kBinaryOp: {
1789 os << "BinaryOp:" << GetBinaryOperationFeedback();
1790 break;
1791 }
1792 case FeedbackSlotKind::kCompareOp: {
1793 os << "CompareOp:" << GetCompareOperationFeedback();
1794 break;
1795 }
1796 case FeedbackSlotKind::kForIn: {
1797 os << "ForIn:" << GetForInFeedback();
1798 break;
1799 }
1800 case FeedbackSlotKind::kLiteral:
1801 break;
1802 case FeedbackSlotKind::kJumpLoop:
1803 os << "JumpLoop";
1804 break;
1805 case FeedbackSlotKind::kInvalid:
1806 UNREACHABLE();
1807 }
1808}

1907static const char* const weekdays[] = {"???", "Sun", "Mon", "Tue",
1908 "Wed", "Thu", "Fri", "Sat"};
1909
1910void JSDate::JSDatePrint(std::ostream& os) {
1911 JSObjectPrintHeader(os, *this, "JSDate");
1912 os << "\n - value: " << value();
1913 if (!IsSmi(year())) {
1914 os << "\n - time = NaN\n";
1915 } else {
1916 // TODO(svenpanne) Add some basic formatting to our streams.
1917 base::ScopedVector<char> buf(100);
1918 SNPrintF(buf, "\n - time = %s %04d/%02d/%02d %02d:%02d:%02d\n",
1919 weekdays[IsSmi(weekday()) ? Smi::ToInt(weekday()) + 1 : 0],
1920 IsSmi(year()) ? Smi::ToInt(year()) : -1,
1921 IsSmi(month()) ? Smi::ToInt(month()) : -1,
1922 IsSmi(day()) ? Smi::ToInt(day()) : -1,
1923 IsSmi(hour()) ? Smi::ToInt(hour()) : -1,
1924 IsSmi(min()) ? Smi::ToInt(min()) : -1,
1925 IsSmi(sec()) ? Smi::ToInt(sec()) : -1);
1926 os << buf.begin();
1927 }
1928 JSObjectPrintBody(os, *this);
1929}

2202
2203void JSFunction::JSFunctionPrint(std::ostream& os) {
2204 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolate();
2205 JSObjectPrintHeader(os, *this, "Function");
2206 os << "\n - function prototype: ";
2207 if (has_prototype_slot()) {
2208 if (has_prototype()) {
2209 os << Brief(prototype());
2210 if (map()->has_non_instance_prototype()) {
2211 os << " (non-instance prototype)";
2212 }
2213 }
2214 os << "\n - initial_map: ";
2215 if (has_initial_map()) os << Brief(initial_map());
2216 } else {
2217 os << "<no-prototype-slot>";
2218 }
2219 os << "\n - shared_info: " << Brief(shared());
2220 os << "\n - name: " << Brief(shared()->Name());
2221
2222 // Print Builtin name for builtin functions
2223 Builtin builtin = code(isolate)->builtin_id();
2224 if (Builtins::IsBuiltinId(builtin)) {
2225 os << "\n - builtin: " << isolate->builtins()->name(builtin);
2226 }
2227
2228 os << "\n - formal_parameter_count: ";
2229 int formal_parameter_count =
2230 shared()->internal_formal_parameter_count_with_receiver();
2231 if (formal_parameter_count == kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel) {
2232 os << "kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel";
2233 } else {
2234 os << formal_parameter_count;
2235 }
2236 os << "\n - kind: " << shared()->kind();
2237 os << "\n - context: " << Brief(context());
2238 os << "\n - code: " << Brief(code(isolate));
2239#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2240 os << "\n - dispatch_handle: 0x" << std::hex << dispatch_handle() << std::dec;
2241 if (has_feedback_vector() &&
2242 raw_feedback_cell()->dispatch_handle() != dispatch_handle()) {
2243 os << "\n - canonical feedback cell dispatch_handle: 0x" << std::hex
2244 << raw_feedback_cell()->dispatch_handle() << std::dec;
2245 }
2246 if (IsTieringRequestedOrInProgress(GetIsolate())) {
2247 os << "\n - tiering request ";
2248 if (tiering_in_progress()) {
2249 os << "in_progress ";
2250 }
2251 IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->PrintCurrentTieringRequest(
2252 dispatch_handle(), GetIsolate(), os);
2253 }
2254
2255#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2256 if (code(isolate)->kind() == CodeKind::FOR_TESTING) {
2257 os << "\n - FOR_TESTING";
2258 } else if (ActiveTierIsIgnition(isolate)) {
2259 os << "\n - interpreted";
2260 if (shared()->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2261 os << "\n - bytecode: " << shared()->GetBytecodeArray(isolate);
2262 }
2263 }
2264#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2265 if (WasmExportedFunction::IsWasmExportedFunction(*this)) {
2266 Tagged<WasmExportedFunction> function = Cast<WasmExportedFunction>(*this);
2267 Tagged<WasmExportedFunctionData> data =
2268 function->shared()->wasm_exported_function_data();
2269 os << "\n - Wasm instance data: " << Brief(data->instance_data());
2270 os << "\n - Wasm function index: " << data->function_index();
2271 }
2272 if (WasmJSFunction::IsWasmJSFunction(*this)) {
2273 Tagged<WasmJSFunction> function = Cast<WasmJSFunction>(*this);
2274 os << "\n - Wasm wrapper around: "
2275 << Brief(function->shared()->wasm_js_function_data()->GetCallable());
2276 }
2277#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2278 shared()->PrintSourceCode(os);
2279 JSObjectPrintBody(os, *this);
2280 os << " - feedback vector: ";
2281 if (!shared()->HasFeedbackMetadata()) {
2282 os << "feedback metadata is not available in SFI\n";
2283 } else if (has_feedback_vector()) {
2284 feedback_vector()->FeedbackVectorPrint(os);
2285 } else if (has_closure_feedback_cell_array()) {
2286 os << "No feedback vector, but we have a closure feedback cell array\n";
2287 closure_feedback_cell_array()->ClosureFeedbackCellArrayPrint(os);
2288 } else {
2289 os << "not available\n";
2290 }
2291}
2292
2293void SharedFunctionInfo::PrintSourceCode(std::ostream& os) {
2294 if (HasSourceCode()) {
2295 os << "\n - source code: ";
2296 Tagged<String> source = Cast<String>(Cast<Script>(script())->source());
2297 int start = StartPosition();
2298 int length = EndPosition() - start;
2299 std::unique_ptr<char[]> source_string = source->ToCString(start, length);
2300 os << source_string.get();
2301 }
2302}
2303
2304void SharedFunctionInfo::SharedFunctionInfoPrint(std::ostream& os) {
2305 PrintHeader(os, "SharedFunctionInfo");
2306 os << "\n - name: ";
2307 if (HasSharedName()) {
2308 os << Brief(Name());
2309 } else {
2310 os << "<no-shared-name>";
2311 }
2312 if (HasInferredName()) {
2313 os << "\n - inferred name: " << Brief(inferred_name());
2314 }
2315 if (class_scope_has_private_brand()) {
2316 os << "\n - class_scope_has_private_brand";
2317 }
2318 if (has_static_private_methods_or_accessors()) {
2319 os << "\n - has_static_private_methods_or_accessors";
2320 }
2321 if (private_name_lookup_skips_outer_class()) {
2322 os << "\n - private_name_lookup_skips_outer_class";
2323 }
2324 os << "\n - kind: " << kind();
2325 os << "\n - syntax kind: " << syntax_kind();
2326 os << "\n - function_map_index: " << function_map_index();
2327 os << "\n - formal_parameter_count: ";
2328 int formal_parameter_count = internal_formal_parameter_count_with_receiver();
2329 if (formal_parameter_count == kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel) {
2330 os << "kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel";
2331 } else {
2332 os << formal_parameter_count;
2333 }
2334 os << "\n - expected_nof_properties: "
2335 << static_cast<int>(expected_nof_properties());
2336 os << "\n - language_mode: " << language_mode();
2337 if (HasTrustedData()) {
2338 os << "\n - trusted_function_data: "
2339 << Brief(GetTrustedData(GetIsolateForSandbox(*this)));
2340 } else {
2341 os << "\n - trusted_function_data: <empty>";
2342 }
2343 os << "\n - untrusted_function_data: " << Brief(GetUntrustedData());
2344 os << "\n - code (from function_data): ";
2345 Isolate* isolate;
2346 if (GetIsolateFromHeapObject(*this, &isolate)) {
2347 os << Brief(GetCode(isolate));
2348 } else {
2349 os << kUnavailableString;
2350 }
2351 PrintSourceCode(os);
2352 // Script files are often large, thus only print their {Brief} representation.
2353 os << "\n - script: " << Brief(script());
2354 os << "\n - function token position: " << function_token_position();
2355 os << "\n - start position: " << StartPosition();
2356 os << "\n - end position: " << EndPosition();
2357 os << "\n - scope info: " << Brief(scope_info());
2358 if (HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
2359 os << "\n - outer scope info: " << Brief(GetOuterScopeInfo());
2360 }
2361 os << "\n - length: " << length();
2362 os << "\n - feedback_metadata: ";
2363 if (HasFeedbackMetadata()) {
2364 feedback_metadata()->FeedbackMetadataPrint(os);
2365 } else {
2366 os << "<none>";
2367 }
2368 os << "\n - function_literal_id: " << function_literal_id();
2369 os << "\n - unique_id: " << unique_id();
2370 os << "\n - age: " << age();
2371 os << "\n";
2372}

2412 code(kAcquireLoad)->CodePrint(os);
2413}
2414
2415void Code::CodePrint(std::ostream& os, const char* name, Address current_pc) {
2416 // This prints the entire {Code,InstructionStream} composite object.
2417 //
2418 // First, Code:
2419 PrintHeader(os, "Code");
2420 os << "\n - kind: " << CodeKindToString(kind());
2421 if (is_builtin()) {
2422 os << "\n - builtin_id: " << Builtins::name(builtin_id());
2423 }
2424 os << "\n - deoptimization_data_or_interpreter_data: "
2425 << Brief(raw_deoptimization_data_or_interpreter_data());
2426 os << "\n - position_table: " << Brief(raw_position_table());
2427 os << "\n - parameter_count: " << parameter_count();
2428 os << "\n - instruction_stream: " << Brief(raw_instruction_stream());
2429 os << "\n - instruction_start: "
2430 << reinterpret_cast<void*>(instruction_start());
2431 os << "\n - is_turbofanned: " << is_turbofanned();
2432 os << "\n - stack_slots: " << stack_slots();
2433 os << "\n - marked_for_deoptimization: " << marked_for_deoptimization();
2434 os << "\n - embedded_objects_cleared: " << embedded_objects_cleared();
2435 os << "\n - can_have_weak_objects: " << can_have_weak_objects();
2436 os << "\n - instruction_size: " << instruction_size();
2437 os << "\n - metadata_size: " << metadata_size();
2438
2439 if (kind() != CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION) {
2440 os << "\n - inlined_bytecode_size: " << inlined_bytecode_size();
2441 } else {
2442 os << "\n - wasm_js_tagged_parameter_count: "
2443 << wasm_js_tagged_parameter_count();
2444 os << "\n - wasm_js_first_tagged_parameter: "
2445 << wasm_js_first_tagged_parameter();
2446 }
2447 os << "\n - osr_offset: " << osr_offset();
2448 os << "\n - handler_table_offset: " << handler_table_offset();
2449 os << "\n - unwinding_info_offset: " << unwinding_info_offset();
2450 if (V8_EMBEDDED_CONSTANT_POOL_BOOL) {
2451 os << "\n - constant_pool_offset: " << constant_pool_offset();
2452 }
2453 os << "\n - code_comments_offset: " << code_comments_offset();
2454
2455 // Then, InstructionStream:
2456 if (has_instruction_stream()) {
2457 Tagged<InstructionStream> istream = instruction_stream();
2458 os << "\n - instruction_stream.relocation_info: "
2459 << Brief(istream->relocation_info());
2460 os << "\n - instruction_stream.body_size: " << istream->body_size();
2461 }
2462 os << "\n";
2463
2464 // Finally, the disassembly:
2465#ifdef ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
2466 os << "\n--- Disassembly: ---\n";
2467 Disassemble(name, os, Isolate::Current(), current_pc);
2468#endif
2469}

2585void WasmStruct::WasmStructPrint(std::ostream& os) {
2586 PrintHeader(os, "WasmStruct");
2587 wasm::StructType* struct_type = type();
2588 os << "\n - fields (" << struct_type->field_count() << "):";
2589 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < struct_type->field_count(); i++) {
2590 wasm::ValueType field = struct_type->field(i);
2591 os << "\n - " << field.short_name() << ": ";
2592 uint32_t field_offset = struct_type->field_offset(i);
2593 Address field_address = RawFieldAddress(field_offset);
2594 switch (field.kind()) {
2595 case wasm::kI32:
2596 os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<int32_t>(field_address);
2597 break;
2598 case wasm::kI64:
2599 os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<int64_t>(field_address);
2600 break;
2601 case wasm::kF16:
2602 os << fp16_ieee_to_fp32_value(
2603 base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint16_t>(field_address));
2604 break;
2605 case wasm::kF32:
2606 os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<float>(field_address);
2607 break;
2608 case wasm::kF64:
2609 os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<double>(field_address);
2610 break;
2611 case wasm::kI8:
2612 os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<int8_t>(field_address);
2613 break;
2614 case wasm::kI16:
2615 os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<int16_t>(field_address);
2616 break;
2617 case wasm::kRef:
2618 case wasm::kRefNull:
2619 case wasm::kRtt: {
2620 Tagged_t raw = base::ReadUnalignedValue<Tagged_t>(field_address);
2621#if V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
2622 Address obj = V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(address(), raw);
2623#else
2624 Address obj = raw;
2625#endif
2626 os << Brief(Tagged<Object>(obj));
2627 break;
2628 }
2629 case wasm::kS128:
2630 os << "0x" << std::hex << std::setfill('0');
2631#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
2632 for (int j = 0; j < kSimd128Size; j++) {
2633#else
2634 for (int j = kSimd128Size - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
2635#endif
2636 os << std::setw(2)
2637 << static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(field_address)[j]);
2638 }
2639 os << std::dec << std::setfill(' ');
2640 break;
2641 case wasm::kTop:
2642 case wasm::kBottom:
2643 case wasm::kVoid:
2644 UNREACHABLE();
2645 }
2646 }
2647 os << "\n";
2648}

2650void WasmArray::WasmArrayPrint(std::ostream& os) {
2651 PrintHeader(os, "WasmArray");
2652 wasm::ArrayType* array_type = type();
2653 uint32_t len = length();
2654 os << "\n - element type: " << array_type->element_type().name();
2655 os << "\n - length: " << len;
2656 Address data_ptr = ptr() + WasmArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag;
2657 switch (array_type->element_type().kind()) {
2658 case wasm::kI32:
2659 PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<int32_t*>(data_ptr), len,
2660 true);
2661 break;
2662 case wasm::kI64:
2663 PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(data_ptr), len,
2664 true);
2665 break;
2666 case wasm::kF16:
2667 PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<Fp16Printer*>(data_ptr), len,
2668 true);
2669 break;
2670 case wasm::kF32:
2671 PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<float*>(data_ptr), len,
2672 true);
2673 break;
2674 case wasm::kF64:
2675 PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<double*>(data_ptr), len,
2676 true);
2677 break;
2678 case wasm::kI8:
2679 PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<int8_t*>(data_ptr), len,
2680 true);
2681 break;
2682 case wasm::kI16:
2683 PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<int16_t*>(data_ptr), len,
2684 true);
2685 break;
2686 case wasm::kRef:
2687 case wasm::kRefNull: {
2688 os << "\n - elements:";
2689 constexpr uint32_t kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements = 5;
2690 for (uint32_t i = 0;
2691 i < std::min(this->length(), kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements);
2692 i++) {
2693 os << "\n " << static_cast<int>(i) << " - "
2694 << Brief(TaggedField<Object>::load(*this, this->element_offset(i)));
2695 }
2696 if (this->length() > kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements) os << "\n ...";
2697 break;
2698 }
2699 case wasm::kS128: {
2700 os << "\n - elements:";
2701 constexpr uint32_t kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements = 5;
2702 for (uint32_t i = 0;
2703 i < std::min(this->length(), kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements);
2704 i++) {
2705 os << "\n " << static_cast<int>(i) << " - 0x" << std::hex
2706 << std::setfill('0');
2707#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
2708 for (int j = 0; j < kSimd128Size; j++) {
2709#else
2710 for (int j = kSimd128Size - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
2711#endif
2712 os << std::setw(2)
2713 << static_cast<int>(
2714 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this->ElementAddress(i))[j]);
2715 }
2716 os << std::dec << std::setfill(' ');
2717 }
2718 if (this->length() > kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements) os << "\n ...";
2719 break;
2720 }
2721 case wasm::kRtt:
2722 case wasm::kTop:
2723 case wasm::kBottom:
2724 case wasm::kVoid:
2725 UNREACHABLE();
2726 }
2727 os << "\n";
2728}

2954void LoadHandler::LoadHandlerPrint(std::ostream& os) {

3236void PrintScopeInfoList(Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info, std::ostream& os,
3237 const char* list_name, int length) {
3238 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3239 if (length <= 0) return;
3240 os << "\n - " << list_name;
3241 os << " {\n";
3242 for (auto it : ScopeInfo::IterateLocalNames(scope_info, no_gc)) {
3243 os << " - " << it->index() << ": " << it->name() << "\n";
3244 }
3245 os << " }";
3246}

3248
3249void ScopeInfo::ScopeInfoPrint(std::ostream& os) {
3250 PrintHeader(os, "ScopeInfo");
3251 if (this->IsEmpty()) {
3252 os << "\n - empty\n";
3253 return;
3254 }
3255 int flags = Flags();
3256
3257 os << "\n - parameters: " << ParameterCount();
3258 os << "\n - context locals : " << ContextLocalCount();
3259 if (HasInlinedLocalNames()) {
3260 os << "\n - inlined local names";
3261 } else {
3262 os << "\n - local names in a hashtable: "
3263 << Brief(context_local_names_hashtable());
3264 }
3265
3266 os << "\n - scope type: " << scope_type();
3267 if (SloppyEvalCanExtendVars()) {
3268 os << "\n - sloppy eval";
3269 os << "\n - dependent code: " << Brief(dependent_code());
3270 }
3271 os << "\n - language mode: " << language_mode();
3272 if (is_declaration_scope()) os << "\n - declaration scope";
3273 if (HasReceiver()) {
3274 os << "\n - receiver: " << ReceiverVariableBits::decode(flags);
3275 }
3276 if (ClassScopeHasPrivateBrand()) os << "\n - class scope has private brand";
3277 if (HasSavedClassVariable()) os << "\n - has saved class variable";
3278 if (HasNewTarget()) os << "\n - needs new target";
3279 if (HasFunctionName()) {
3280 os << "\n - function name(" << FunctionVariableBits::decode(flags) << "): ";
3281 ShortPrint(FunctionName(), os);
3282 }
3283 if (IsAsmModule()) os << "\n - asm module";
3284 if (HasSimpleParameters()) os << "\n - simple parameters";
3285 if (PrivateNameLookupSkipsOuterClass())
3286 os << "\n - private name lookup skips outer class";
3287 os << "\n - function kind: " << function_kind();
3288 if (HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
3289 os << "\n - outer scope info: " << Brief(OuterScopeInfo());
3290 }
3291 if (HasFunctionName()) {
3292 os << "\n - function name: " << Brief(FunctionName());
3293 }
3294 if (HasInferredFunctionName()) {
3295 os << "\n - inferred function name: " << Brief(InferredFunctionName());
3296 }
3297 if (HasContextExtensionSlot()) {
3298 os << "\n - has context extension slot";
3299 }
3300
3301 if (HasPositionInfo()) {
3302 os << "\n - start position: " << StartPosition();
3303 os << "\n - end position: " << EndPosition();
3304 }
3305 os << "\n - length: " << length();
3306 if (length() > 0) {
3307 PrintScopeInfoList(*this, os, "context slots", ContextLocalCount());
3308 // TODO(neis): Print module stuff if present.
3309 }
3310 os << "\n";
3311}

3348void HeapObject::HeapObjectShortPrint(std::ostream& os) {
3349 PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase();
3350 os << AsHex::Address(this->ptr()) << " ";
3351
3352 if (IsString(*this, cage_base)) {
3353 HeapStringAllocator allocator;
3354 StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
3355 Cast<String>(*this)->StringShortPrint(&accumulator);
3356 os << accumulator.ToCString().get();
3357 return;
3358 }
3359 if (IsJSObject(*this, cage_base)) {
3360 HeapStringAllocator allocator;
3361 StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
3362 Cast<JSObject>(*this)->JSObjectShortPrint(&accumulator);
3363 os << accumulator.ToCString().get();
3364 return;
3365 }
3366
3367 InstanceType instance_type = map(cage_base)->instance_type();
3368
3369 // Skip invalid trusted objects. Technically it'd be fine to still handle
3370 // them below since we only print the objects, but such an object will
3371 // quickly lead to out-of-sandbox segfaults and so fuzzers will complain.
3372 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsTrustedObject(instance_type) &&
3373 !OutsideSandboxOrInReadonlySpace(*this)) {
3374 os << "<Invalid TrustedObject (outside trusted space)>\n";
3375 return;
3376 }
3377
3378 switch (instance_type) {
3379 case MAP_TYPE: {
3380 Tagged<Map> map = Cast<Map>(*this);
3381 if (map->instance_type() == MAP_TYPE) {
3382 // This is one of the meta maps, print only relevant fields.
3383 os << "<MetaMap (" << Brief(map->native_context_or_null()) << ")>";
3384 } else {
3385 os << "<Map";
3386 if (map->instance_size() != kVariableSizeSentinel) {
3387 os << "[" << map->instance_size() << "]";
3388 }
3389 os << "(";
3390 if (IsJSObjectMap(map)) {
3391 os << ElementsKindToString(map->elements_kind());
3392 } else {
3393 os << map->instance_type();
3394 }
3395 os << ")>";
3396 }
3397 } break;
3398 case AWAIT_CONTEXT_TYPE: {
3399 os << "<AwaitContext generator= ";
3400 HeapStringAllocator allocator;
3401 StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
3402 ShortPrint(Cast<Context>(*this)->extension(), &accumulator);
3403 os << accumulator.ToCString().get();
3404 os << '>';
3405 break;
3406 }
3407 case BLOCK_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3408 os << "<BlockContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3409 break;
3410 case CATCH_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3411 os << "<CatchContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3412 break;
3413 case DEBUG_EVALUATE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3414 os << "<DebugEvaluateContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3415 break;
3416 case EVAL_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3417 os << "<EvalContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3418 break;
3419 case FUNCTION_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3420 os << "<FunctionContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3421 break;
3422 case MODULE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3423 os << "<ModuleContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3424 break;
3425 case NATIVE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3426 os << "<NativeContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3427 break;
3428 case SCRIPT_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3429 os << "<ScriptContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3430 break;
3431 case WITH_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3432 os << "<WithContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3433 break;
3434 case SCRIPT_CONTEXT_TABLE_TYPE:
3435 os << "<ScriptContextTable["
3436 << Cast<ScriptContextTable>(*this)->capacity() << "]>";
3437 break;
3438 case HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
3439 os << "<HashTable[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3440 break;
3441 case ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
3442 os << "<OrderedHashMap[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3443 break;
3444 case ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
3445 os << "<OrderedHashSet[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3446 break;
3447 case ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
3448 os << "<OrderedNameDictionary[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length()
3449 << "]>";
3450 break;
3451 case NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
3452 os << "<NameDictionary[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3453 break;
3454 case SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
3455 os << "<SwissNameDictionary["
3456 << Cast<SwissNameDictionary>(*this)->Capacity() << "]>";
3457 break;
3458 case GLOBAL_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
3459 os << "<GlobalDictionary[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3460 break;
3461 case NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
3462 os << "<NumberDictionary[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3463 break;
3464 case SIMPLE_NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
3465 os << "<SimpleNumberDictionary[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length()
3466 << "]>";
3467 break;
3468 case FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE:
3469 os << "<FixedArray[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3470 break;
3471 case OBJECT_BOILERPLATE_DESCRIPTION_TYPE:
3472 os << "<ObjectBoilerplateDescription["
3473 << Cast<ObjectBoilerplateDescription>(*this)->capacity() << "]>";
3474 break;
3475 case FIXED_DOUBLE_ARRAY_TYPE:
3476 os << "<FixedDoubleArray[" << Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(*this)->length()
3477 << "]>";
3478 break;
3479 case BYTE_ARRAY_TYPE:
3480 os << "<ByteArray[" << Cast<ByteArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3481 break;
3482 case BYTECODE_ARRAY_TYPE:
3483 os << "<BytecodeArray[" << Cast<BytecodeArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3484 break;
3485 case DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
3486 os << "<DescriptorArray["
3487 << Cast<DescriptorArray>(*this)->number_of_descriptors() << "]>";
3488 break;
3489 case WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE:
3490 os << "<WeakFixedArray[" << Cast<WeakFixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3491 break;
3492 case TRUSTED_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE:
3493 os << "<TrustedFixedArray[" << Cast<TrustedFixedArray>(*this)->length()
3494 << "]>";
3495 break;
3496 case TRUSTED_WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE:
3497 os << "<TrustedWeakFixedArray["
3498 << Cast<TrustedWeakFixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3499 break;
3500 case PROTECTED_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE:
3501 os << "<ProtectedFixedArray["
3502 << Cast<ProtectedFixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3503 break;
3504 case PROTECTED_WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE:
3505 os << "<ProtectedWeakFixedArray["
3506 << Cast<ProtectedWeakFixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3507 break;
3508 case TRANSITION_ARRAY_TYPE:
3509 os << "<TransitionArray[" << Cast<TransitionArray>(*this)->length()
3510 << "]>";
3511 break;
3512 case PROPERTY_ARRAY_TYPE:
3513 os << "<PropertyArray[" << Cast<PropertyArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3514 break;
3515 case FEEDBACK_CELL_TYPE: {
3516 {
3517 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
3518 os << "<FeedbackCell[";
3519 if (map() == roots.no_closures_cell_map()) {
3520 os << "no feedback";
3521 } else if (map() == roots.one_closure_cell_map()) {
3522 os << "one closure";
3523 } else if (map() == roots.many_closures_cell_map()) {
3524 os << "many closures";
3525 } else {
3526 os << "!!!INVALID MAP!!!";
3527 }
3528 os << "]>";
3529 }
3530 break;
3531 }
3532 case CLOSURE_FEEDBACK_CELL_ARRAY_TYPE:
3533 os << "<ClosureFeedbackCellArray["
3534 << Cast<ClosureFeedbackCellArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3535 break;
3536 case FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE:
3537 os << "<FeedbackVector[" << Cast<FeedbackVector>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3538 break;
3539 case FREE_SPACE_TYPE:
3540 os << "<FreeSpace[" << Cast<FreeSpace>(*this)->size(kRelaxedLoad) << "]>";
3541 break;
3542
3543 case PREPARSE_DATA_TYPE: {
3544 Tagged<PreparseData> data = Cast<PreparseData>(*this);
3545 os << "<PreparseData[data=" << data->data_length()
3546 << " children=" << data->children_length() << "]>";
3547 break;
3548 }
3549
3550 case UNCOMPILED_DATA_WITHOUT_PREPARSE_DATA_TYPE: {
3551 Tagged<UncompiledDataWithoutPreparseData> data =
3552 Cast<UncompiledDataWithoutPreparseData>(*this);
3553 os << "<UncompiledDataWithoutPreparseData (" << data->start_position()
3554 << ", " << data->end_position() << ")]>";
3555 break;
3556 }
3557
3558 case UNCOMPILED_DATA_WITH_PREPARSE_DATA_TYPE: {
3559 Tagged<UncompiledDataWithPreparseData> data =
3560 Cast<UncompiledDataWithPreparseData>(*this);
3561 os << "<UncompiledDataWithPreparseData (" << data->start_position()
3562 << ", " << data->end_position()
3563 << ") preparsed=" << Brief(data->preparse_data()) << ">";
3564 break;
3565 }
3566
3567 case SHARED_FUNCTION_INFO_TYPE: {
3568 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(*this);
3569 std::unique_ptr<char[]> debug_name = shared->DebugNameCStr();
3570 if (debug_name[0] != '\0') {
3571 os << "<SharedFunctionInfo " << debug_name.get() << ">";
3572 } else {
3573 os << "<SharedFunctionInfo>";
3574 }
3575 break;
3576 }
3577 case JS_MESSAGE_OBJECT_TYPE:
3578 os << "<JSMessageObject>";
3579 break;
3580#define MAKE_STRUCT_CASE(TYPE, Name, name) \
3581 case TYPE: \
3582 os << "<" #Name; \
3583 Cast<Name>(*this)->BriefPrintDetails(os); \
3584 os << ">"; \
3585 break;
3586 STRUCT_LIST(MAKE_STRUCT_CASE)
3587#undef MAKE_STRUCT_CASE
3588 case ALLOCATION_SITE_TYPE: {
3589 os << "<AllocationSite";
3590 Cast<AllocationSite>(*this)->BriefPrintDetails(os);
3591 os << ">";
3592 break;
3593 }
3594 case SCOPE_INFO_TYPE: {
3595 Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope = Cast<ScopeInfo>(*this);
3596 os << "<ScopeInfo";
3597 if (!scope->IsEmpty()) os << " " << scope->scope_type();
3598 os << ">";
3599 break;
3600 }
3601 case CODE_TYPE: {
3602 Tagged<Code> code = Cast<Code>(*this);
3603 os << "<Code " << CodeKindToString(code->kind());
3604 if (code->is_builtin()) {
3605 os << " " << Builtins::name(code->builtin_id());
3606 }
3607 os << ">";
3608 break;
3609 }
3610 case HOLE_TYPE: {
3611#define PRINT_HOLE(Type, Value, _) \
3612 if (Is##Type(*this)) { \
3613 os << "<" #Value ">"; \
3614 break; \
3615 }
3616 HOLE_LIST(PRINT_HOLE)
3617#undef PRINT_HOLE
3618 UNREACHABLE();
3619 }
3620 case INSTRUCTION_STREAM_TYPE: {
3621 Tagged<InstructionStream> istream = Cast<InstructionStream>(*this);
3622 Tagged<Code> code = istream->code(kAcquireLoad);
3623 os << "<InstructionStream " << CodeKindToString(code->kind());
3624 if (code->is_builtin()) {
3625 os << " " << Builtins::name(code->builtin_id());
3626 }
3627 os << ">";
3628 break;
3629 }
3630 case ODDBALL_TYPE: {
3631 if (IsUndefined(*this)) {
3632 os << "<undefined>";
3633 } else if (IsNull(*this)) {
3634 os << "<null>";
3635 } else if (IsTrue(*this)) {
3636 os << "<true>";
3637 } else if (IsFalse(*this)) {
3638 os << "<false>";
3639 } else {
3640 os << "<Odd Oddball: ";
3641 os << Cast<Oddball>(*this)->to_string()->ToCString().get();
3642 os << ">";
3643 }
3644 break;
3645 }
3646 case SYMBOL_TYPE: {
3647 Tagged<Symbol> symbol = Cast<Symbol>(*this);
3648 symbol->SymbolShortPrint(os);
3649 break;
3650 }
3651 case HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE: {
3652 os << "<HeapNumber ";
3653 Cast<HeapNumber>(*this)->HeapNumberShortPrint(os);
3654 os << ">";
3655 break;
3656 }
3657 case BIGINT_TYPE: {
3658 os << "<BigInt ";
3659 Cast<BigInt>(*this)->BigIntShortPrint(os);
3660 os << ">";
3661 break;
3662 }
3663 case JS_PROXY_TYPE:
3664 os << "<JSProxy>";
3665 break;
3666 case FOREIGN_TYPE:
3667 os << "<Foreign>";
3668 break;
3669 case CELL_TYPE: {
3670 os << "<Cell value= ";
3671 HeapStringAllocator allocator;
3672 StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
3673 ShortPrint(Cast<Cell>(*this)->value(), &accumulator);
3674 os << accumulator.ToCString().get();
3675 os << '>';
3676 break;
3677 }
3678 case PROPERTY_CELL_TYPE: {
3679 Tagged<PropertyCell> cell = Cast<PropertyCell>(*this);
3680 os << "<PropertyCell name=";
3681 ShortPrint(cell->name(), os);
3682 os << " value=";
3683 HeapStringAllocator allocator;
3684 StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
3685 ShortPrint(cell->value(kAcquireLoad), &accumulator);
3686 os << accumulator.ToCString().get();
3687 os << '>';
3688 break;
3689 }
3690 case CONTEXT_SIDE_PROPERTY_CELL_TYPE: {
3691 os << "<ContextSidePropertyCell>";
3692 break;
3693 }
3694 case ACCESSOR_INFO_TYPE: {
3695 Tagged<AccessorInfo> info = Cast<AccessorInfo>(*this);
3696 os << "<AccessorInfo ";
3697 os << "name= " << Brief(info->name());
3698 os << ", data= " << Brief(info->data());
3699 os << ">";
3700 break;
3701 }
3702 case FUNCTION_TEMPLATE_INFO_TYPE: {
3703 Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> info = Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(*this);
3704 os << "<FunctionTemplateInfo ";
3705 Isolate* isolate;
3706 if (GetIsolateFromHeapObject(*this, &isolate)) {
3707 os << "callback= " << reinterpret_cast<void*>(info->callback(isolate));
3708 } else {
3709 os << "callback= " << kUnavailableString;
3710 }
3711 os << ", data= " << Brief(info->callback_data(kAcquireLoad));
3712 os << ", has_side_effects= ";
3713 if (info->has_side_effects()) {
3714 os << "true>";
3715 } else {
3716 os << "false>";
3717 }
3718 break;
3719 }
3720#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3721 case WASM_DISPATCH_TABLE_TYPE:
3722 os << "<WasmDispatchTable[" << Cast<WasmDispatchTable>(*this)->length()
3723 << "]>";
3724 break;
3725#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3726 default:
3727 os << "<Other heap object (" << map()->instance_type() << ")>";
3728 break;
3729 }
3730}
3731
3732void HeapNumber::HeapNumberShortPrint(std::ostream& os) {
3733 static constexpr uint64_t kUint64AllBitsSet =
3734 static_cast<uint64_t>(int64_t{-1});
3735 // Min/max integer values representable by 52 bits of mantissa and 1 sign bit.
3736 static constexpr int64_t kMinSafeInteger =
3737 static_cast<int64_t>(kUint64AllBitsSet << 53);
3738 static constexpr int64_t kMaxSafeInteger = -(kMinSafeInteger + 1);
3739
3740 double val = value();
3741 if (i::IsMinusZero(val)) {
3742 os << "-0.0";
3743 } else if (val == DoubleToInteger(val) &&
3744 val >= static_cast<double>(kMinSafeInteger) &&
3745 val <= static_cast<double>(kMaxSafeInteger)) {
3746 // Print integer HeapNumbers in safe integer range with max precision: as
3747 // 9007199254740991.0 instead of 9.0072e+15
3748 int64_t i = static_cast<int64_t>(val);
3749 os << i << ".0";
3750 } else {
3751 os << val;
3752 }
3753}

3756void Name::NameShortPrint() {
3757 if (IsString(this)) {
3758 PrintF("%s", Cast<String>(this)->ToCString().get());
3759 } else {
3760 DCHECK(IsSymbol(this));
3761 Tagged<Symbol> s = Cast<Symbol>(this);
3762 if (IsUndefined(s->description())) {
3763 PrintF("#<%s>", s->PrivateSymbolToName());
3764 } else {
3765 PrintF("<%s>", Cast<String>(s->description())->ToCString().get());
3766 }
3767 }
3768}

3772 if (IsString(this)) {

3774 } else {
3775 DCHECK(IsSymbol(this));
3776 Tagged<Symbol> s = Cast<Symbol>(this);
3777 if (IsUndefined(s->description())) {
3778 return SNPrintF(str, "#<%s>", s->PrivateSymbolToName());
3779 } else {
3780 return SNPrintF(str, "<%s>",
3781 Cast<String>(s->description())->ToCString().get());
3782 }

3803
3804void Map::MapPrint(std::ostream& os) {
3805 bool is_meta_map = instance_type() == MAP_TYPE;
3806#ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
3807 PrintHeader(os, is_meta_map ? "MetaMap" : "Map");
3808#else
3809 os << (is_meta_map ? "MetaMap=" : "Map=") << reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptr());
3810#endif
3811 os << "\n - type: " << instance_type();
3812 os << "\n - instance size: ";
3813 if (instance_size() == kVariableSizeSentinel) {
3814 os << "variable";
3815 } else {
3816 os << instance_size();
3817 }
3818 if (is_meta_map) {
3819 // This is one of the meta maps, print only relevant fields.
3820 os << "\n - native_context: " << Brief(native_context_or_null());
3821 os << "\n";
3822 return;
3823 }
3824
3825 if (IsJSObjectMap(*this)) {
3826 os << "\n - inobject properties: " << GetInObjectProperties();
3827 os << "\n - unused property fields: " << UnusedPropertyFields();
3828 }
3829 os << "\n - elements kind: " << ElementsKindToString(elements_kind());
3830 os << "\n - enum length: ";
3831 if (EnumLength() == kInvalidEnumCacheSentinel) {
3832 os << "invalid";
3833 } else {
3834 os << EnumLength();
3835 }
3836 if (is_deprecated()) os << "\n - deprecated_map";
3837 if (is_stable()) os << "\n - stable_map";
3838 if (is_migration_target()) os << "\n - migration_target";
3839 if (is_dictionary_map()) os << "\n - dictionary_map";
3840 if (has_named_interceptor()) os << "\n - named_interceptor";
3841 if (has_indexed_interceptor()) os << "\n - indexed_interceptor";
3842 if (may_have_interesting_properties())
3843 os << "\n - may_have_interesting_properties";
3844 if (is_undetectable()) os << "\n - undetectable";
3845 if (is_callable()) os << "\n - callable";
3846 if (is_constructor()) os << "\n - constructor";
3847 if (has_prototype_slot()) {
3848 os << "\n - has_prototype_slot";
3849 if (has_non_instance_prototype()) os << " (non-instance prototype)";
3850 }
3851 if (is_access_check_needed()) os << "\n - access_check_needed";
3852 if (!is_extensible()) os << "\n - non-extensible";
3853 if (IsContextMap(*this)) {
3854 os << "\n - native context: " << Brief(native_context());
3855 } else if (is_prototype_map()) {
3856 os << "\n - prototype_map";
3857 os << "\n - prototype info: " << Brief(prototype_info());
3858 } else {
3859 os << "\n - back pointer: " << Brief(GetBackPointer());
3860 }
3861 os << "\n - prototype_validity cell: "
3862 << Brief(prototype_validity_cell(kRelaxedLoad));
3863 os << "\n - instance descriptors " << (owns_descriptors() ? "(own) " : "")
3864 << "#" << NumberOfOwnDescriptors() << ": "
3865 << Brief(instance_descriptors());
3866
3867 // Read-only maps can't have transitions, which is fortunate because we need
3868 // the isolate to iterate over the transitions.
3869 if (!HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*this)) {
3870 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolateFromWritableObject(*this);
3871 TransitionsAccessor transitions(isolate, *this);
3872 int nof_transitions = transitions.NumberOfTransitions();
3873 if (nof_transitions > 0 || transitions.HasPrototypeTransitions() ||
3874 transitions.HasSideStepTransitions()) {
3875 os << "\n - transitions #" << nof_transitions << ": ";
3876 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
3877 Tagged<Smi> smi;
3878 if (raw_transitions().ToSmi(&smi)) {
3879 os << Brief(smi);
3880 } else if (raw_transitions().GetHeapObject(&heap_object)) {
3881 os << Brief(heap_object);
3882 }
3883#ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
3884 transitions.PrintTransitions(os);
3885#endif // OBJECT_PRINT
3886 }
3887 }
3888 os << "\n - prototype: " << Brief(prototype());
3889 if (has_non_instance_prototype()) {
3890 os << "\n - non-instance prototype: " << Brief(GetNonInstancePrototype());
3891 }
3892 if (!IsContextMap(*this)) {
3893 os << "\n - constructor: " << Brief(GetConstructor());
3894 }
3895 os << "\n - dependent code: " << Brief(dependent_code());
3896 os << "\n - construction counter: " << construction_counter();
3897 os << "\n";
3898}

3900void DescriptorArray::PrintDescriptors(std::ostream& os) {
3901 for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(number_of_descriptors())) {
3902 Tagged<Name> key = GetKey(i);
3903 os << "\n [" << i.as_int() << "]: ";
3904#ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
3905 key->NamePrint(os);
3906#else
3907 ShortPrint(key, os);
3908#endif
3909 os << " ";
3910 PrintDescriptorDetails(os, i, PropertyDetails::kPrintFull);
3911 }
3912 os << "\n";
3913}
3914
3915void DescriptorArray::PrintDescriptorDetails(std::ostream& os,
3916 InternalIndex descriptor,
3917 PropertyDetails::PrintMode mode) {
3918 PropertyDetails details = GetDetails(descriptor);
3919 details.PrintAsFastTo(os, mode);
3920 os << " @ ";
3921 switch (details.location()) {
3922 case PropertyLocation::kField: {
3923 Tagged<FieldType> field_type = GetFieldType(descriptor);
3924 FieldType::PrintTo(field_type, os);
3925 break;
3926 }
3927 case PropertyLocation::kDescriptor:
3928 Tagged<Object> value = GetStrongValue(descriptor);
3929 os << Brief(value);
3930 if (IsAccessorPair(value)) {
3931 Tagged<AccessorPair> pair = Cast<AccessorPair>(value);
3932 os << "(get: " << Brief(pair->getter())
3933 << ", set: " << Brief(pair->setter()) << ")";
3934 }
3935 break;
3936 }
3937}

3939#if defined(DEBUG) || defined(OBJECT_PRINT)
3940// This method is only meant to be called from gdb for debugging purposes.
3941// Since the string can also be in two-byte encoding, non-Latin1 characters
3942// will be ignored in the output.
3943char* String::ToAsciiArray() {
3944 // Static so that subsequent calls frees previously allocated space.
3945 // This also means that previous results will be overwritten.
3946 static char* buffer = nullptr;
3947 if (buffer != nullptr) delete[] buffer;
3948 buffer = new char[length() + 1];
3949 WriteToFlat(this, reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(buffer), 0, length());
3950 buffer[length()] = 0;
3951 return buffer;
3952}
