3954// static
3955void TransitionsAccessor::PrintOneTransition(std::ostream& os, Tagged<Name> key,
3956 Tagged<Map> target) {
3957 os << "\n ";
3958#ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
3959 key->NamePrint(os);
3960#else
3961 ShortPrint(key, os);
3962#endif
3963 os << ": ";
3964 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
3965 if (key == roots.nonextensible_symbol()) {
3966 os << "(transition to non-extensible)";
3967 } else if (key == roots.sealed_symbol()) {
3968 os << "(transition to sealed)";
3969 } else if (key == roots.frozen_symbol()) {
3970 os << "(transition to frozen)";
3971 } else if (key == roots.elements_transition_symbol()) {
3972 os << "(transition to " << ElementsKindToString(target->elements_kind())
3973 << ")";
3974 } else if (key == roots.strict_function_transition_symbol()) {
3975 os << " (transition to strict function)";
3976 } else {
3977 DCHECK(!IsSpecialTransition(roots, key));
3978 os << "(transition to ";
3979 InternalIndex descriptor = target->LastAdded();
3980 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = target->instance_descriptors();
3981 descriptors->PrintDescriptorDetails(os, descriptor,
3982 PropertyDetails::kForTransitions);
3983 os << ")";
3984 }
3985 os << " -> " << Brief(target);
3986}
3987
3988void TransitionArray::PrintInternal(std::ostream& os) {
3989 {
3990 int num_transitions = number_of_transitions();
3991 os << "\n Transitions #" << num_transitions << ":";
3992 for (int i = 0; i < num_transitions; i++) {
3993 Tagged<Name> key = GetKey(i);
3994 Tagged<Map> target;
3995 GetTargetIfExists(i, GetIsolateFromWritableObject(*this), &target);
3996 TransitionsAccessor::PrintOneTransition(os, key, target);
3997 }
3998 }
3999
4000 if (HasPrototypeTransitions()) {
4001 auto prototype_transitions = GetPrototypeTransitions();
4002 int num_transitions = NumberOfPrototypeTransitions(prototype_transitions);
4003 os << "\n Prototype transitions #" << num_transitions << ": "
4004 << Brief(prototype_transitions);
4005 for (int i = 0; i < num_transitions; i++) {
4006 auto maybe = prototype_transitions->get(
4007 TransitionArray::kProtoTransitionHeaderSize + i);
4008 Tagged<HeapObject> target;
4009 if (maybe.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&target)) {
4010 auto map = Cast<Map>(target);
4011 os << "\n " << Brief(map->prototype()) << " -> "
4012 << Brief(Cast<Map>(target));
4013 }
4014 }
4015 }
4016
4017 if (HasSideStepTransitions()) {
4018 auto sidestep_transitions = GetSideStepTransitions();
4019 int num_transitions = sidestep_transitions->length();
4020 os << "\n Sidestep transitions #" << num_transitions << ": "
4021 << Brief(sidestep_transitions);
4022 for (int i = 0; i < num_transitions; i++) {
4023 SideStepTransition::Kind kind = static_cast<SideStepTransition::Kind>(i);
4024 auto maybe_target = sidestep_transitions->get(i);
4025 os << "\n " << kind << " -> " << Brief(maybe_target);
4026 }
4027 }
4028}
4029
4030void TransitionsAccessor::PrintTransitions(std::ostream& os) {
4031 switch (encoding()) {
4032 case kPrototypeInfo:
4033 case kUninitialized:
4034 case kMigrationTarget:
4035 return;
4036 case kWeakRef: {
4037 Tagged<Map> target =
4038 Cast<Map>(raw_transitions_.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
4039 Tagged<Name> key = GetSimpleTransitionKey(target);
4040 PrintOneTransition(os, key, target);
4041 break;
4042 }
4043 case kFullTransitionArray:
4044 return transitions()->PrintInternal(os);
4045 }
4046}

4048void TransitionsAccessor::PrintTransitionTree() {
4049 StdoutStream os;
4050 os << (IsUndefined(map_->GetBackPointer()) ? "root_" : "")
4051 << "map= " << Brief(map_);
4052 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4053 PrintTransitionTree(os, 0, &no_gc);
4054 os << "\n" << std::flush;
4055}
4056
4057void TransitionsAccessor::PrintTransitionTree(
4058 std::ostream& os, int level, DisallowGarbageCollection* no_gc) {
4059 ReadOnlyRoots roots = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate_);
4060 int pos = 0;
4061 int proto_pos = 0;
4062 ForEachTransitionWithKey(
4063 no_gc,
4064 [&](Tagged<Name> key, Tagged<Map> target) {
4065 os << std::endl
4066 << " " << level << "/" << pos << ":" << std::setw(level * 2 + 2)
4067 << " ";
4068 pos++;
4069 std::stringstream ss;
4070 ss << Brief(target);
4071 os << std::left << std::setw(50) << ss.str() << ": ";
4072
4073 if (key == roots.nonextensible_symbol()) {
4074 os << "to non-extensible";
4075 } else if (key == roots.sealed_symbol()) {
4076 os << "to sealed ";
4077 } else if (key == roots.frozen_symbol()) {
4078 os << "to frozen";
4079 } else if (key == roots.elements_transition_symbol()) {
4080 os << "to " << ElementsKindToString(target->elements_kind());
4081 } else if (key == roots.strict_function_transition_symbol()) {
4082 os << "to strict function";
4083 } else {
4084#ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
4085 key->NamePrint(os);
4086#else
4087 ShortPrint(key, os);
4088#endif
4089 os << " ";
4090 DCHECK(!IsSpecialTransition(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate_), key));
4091 os << "to ";
4092 InternalIndex descriptor = target->LastAdded();
4093 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
4094 target->instance_descriptors(isolate_);
4095 descriptors->PrintDescriptorDetails(os, descriptor,
4096 PropertyDetails::kForTransitions);
4097 }
4098 TransitionsAccessor transitions(isolate_, target);
4099 transitions.PrintTransitionTree(os, level + 1, no_gc);
4100 },
4101 [&](Tagged<Map> target) {
4102 os << std::endl
4103 << " " << level << "/p" << proto_pos << ":"
4104 << std::setw(level * 2 + 2) << " ";
4105 proto_pos++;
4106 std::stringstream ss;
4107 ss << Brief(target);
4108 os << std::left << std::setw(50) << ss.str() << ": to proto ";
4109 ShortPrint(target->prototype(), os);
4110 TransitionsAccessor transitions(isolate_, target);
4111 transitions.PrintTransitionTree(os, level + 1, no_gc);
4112 },
4113 [&](SideStepTransition::Kind kind, Tagged<Object> side_step) {
4114 os << std::endl
4115 << " " << level << "/s:" << std::setw(level * 2 + 2) << " ";
4116 std::stringstream ss;
4117 ss << Brief(side_step);
4118 os << std::left << std::setw(50) << ss.str() << ": sidestep " << kind;
4119 });
4120}
4121
4122void JSObject::PrintTransitions(std::ostream& os) {
4123 TransitionsAccessor ta(GetIsolate(), map());
4124 if (ta.NumberOfTransitions() != 0 || ta.HasPrototypeTransitions()) {
4125 os << "\n - transitions";
4126 ta.PrintTransitions(os);
4127 }
4128}

4130#endif // defined(DEBUG) || defined(OBJECT_PRINT)

4134
4135inline i::Tagged<i::Object> GetObjectFromRaw(void* object) {
4136 i::Address object_ptr = reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(object);
4137#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
4138 if (RoundDown<i::kPtrComprCageBaseAlignment>(object_ptr) == i::kNullAddress) {
4139 // Try to decompress pointer.
4140 i::Isolate* isolate = i::Isolate::TryGetCurrent();
4141 if (isolate != nullptr) {
4142 object_ptr = i::V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(
4143 isolate, static_cast<i::Tagged_t>(object_ptr));
4144 } else {
4145 i::PtrComprCageBase cage_base = i::GetPtrComprCageBase();
4146 object_ptr = i::V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(
4147 cage_base, static_cast<i::Tagged_t>(object_ptr));
4148 }
4149 }
4150#endif
4151 return i::Tagged<i::Object>(object_ptr);
4152}

4199V8_DONT_STRIP_SYMBOL
4200V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE extern void _v8_internal_Print_Code(void* object) {
4201 i::Address address = reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(object);
4202 i::Isolate* isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4203
4204#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4205 {
4206 if (auto* wasm_code =
4207 i::wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate, address)) {
4208 i::StdoutStream os;
4209 wasm_code->Disassemble(nullptr, os, address);
4210 return;
4211 }
4212 }
4213#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4214
4215 std::optional<i::Tagged<i::Code>> lookup_result =
4216 isolate->heap()->TryFindCodeForInnerPointerForPrinting(address);
4217 if (!lookup_result.has_value()) {
4218 i::PrintF(
4219 "%p is not within the current isolate's code or embedded spaces\n",
4220 object);
4221 return;
4222 }
4223
4224#if defined(OBJECT_PRINT)
4225 i::StdoutStream os;
4226 lookup_result.value()->CodePrint(os, nullptr, address);
4227#elif defined(ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER)
4228 i::StdoutStream os;
4229 lookup_result.value()->Disassemble(nullptr, os, isolate, address);
4230#else
4231 i::Print(lookup_result.value());
4232#endif
4233}

4244V8_DONT_STRIP_SYMBOL
4245V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE extern void _v8_internal_Print_OnlyCode(void* object,
4246 size_t range_limit) {
4247 i::Address address = reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(object);
4248 i::Isolate* isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4249
4250#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4251 {
4252 if (i::wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate, address)) {
4253 i::PrintF("Not supported on wasm code");
4254 return;
4255 }
4256 }
4257#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4258
4259 std::optional<i::Tagged<i::Code>> lookup_result =
4260 isolate->heap()->TryFindCodeForInnerPointerForPrinting(address);
4261 if (!lookup_result.has_value()) {
4262 i::PrintF(
4263 "%p is not within the current isolate's code or embedded spaces\n",
4264 object);
4265 return;
4266 }
4267
4268#if defined(ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER)
4269 i::StdoutStream os;
4270 lookup_result.value()->DisassembleOnlyCode(nullptr, os, isolate, address,
4271 range_limit);
4272#endif
4273}

4281namespace _v8_internal_debugonly {
4282// This class is easy to navigate in a GUI debugger and not intended for
4283// use elsewhere.
4284struct StackTraceDebugDetails {
4285 i::StackFrame::Type type;
4286 std::string summary;
4287 std::vector<i::Tagged<i::SharedFunctionInfo>> functions;
4288 std::vector<i::Tagged<i::Object>> expressions;
4289};
4290} // namespace _v8_internal_debugonly
4291
4292// Used by lldb_visualizers.py to create a representation of the V8 stack.
4293V8_DONT_STRIP_SYMBOL
4294V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE extern std::vector<
4295 _v8_internal_debugonly::StackTraceDebugDetails>
4296_v8_internal_Expand_StackTrace(i::Isolate* isolate) {
4297 std::vector<_v8_internal_debugonly::StackTraceDebugDetails> stack;
4298 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4299 int i = 0;
4300
4301 for (i::StackFrameIterator it(isolate); !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
4302 i::CommonFrame* frame = i::CommonFrame::cast(it.frame());
4303 _v8_internal_debugonly::StackTraceDebugDetails details;
4304 details.type = frame->type();
4305
4306 if (frame->is_javascript()) {
4307 i::JavaScriptFrame::cast(frame)->GetFunctions(&details.functions);
4308 if (!frame->is_optimized_js()) {
4309 int exprcount = frame->ComputeExpressionsCount();
4310 for (int i = 0; i < exprcount; i++) {
4311 details.expressions.push_back(frame->GetExpression(i));
4312 }
4313 }
4314 }
4315
4316 i::HandleScope scope(isolate);
4317 i::StringStream::ClearMentionedObjectCache(isolate);
4318 i::HeapStringAllocator allocator;
4319 i::StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
4320 frame->Print(&accumulator, i::StackFrame::OVERVIEW, i++);
4321 std::unique_ptr<char[]> overview = accumulator.ToCString();
4322 details.summary = overview.get();
4323 stack.push_back(std::move(details));
4324 }
4325 return stack;
4326}

4329V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE extern void _v8_internal_Print_TransitionTree(
4330 void* object, bool start_at_root = false) {
4331 i::Tagged<i::Object> o(GetObjectFromRaw(object));
4332 if (!IsMap(o)) {
4333 printf("Please provide a valid Map\n");
4334 } else {
4335#if defined(DEBUG) || defined(OBJECT_PRINT)
4336 i::Tagged<i::Map> map = i::UncheckedCast<i::Map>(o);
4337 i::TransitionsAccessor transitions(
4338 i::Isolate::Current(),
4339 start_at_root ? map->FindRootMap(GetPtrComprCageBase(map)) : map);
4340 transitions.PrintTransitionTree();
4341#endif
4342 }
4343}
